                Heroni Invic<lb break="no" n="2"/>to Sicinius <lb n="3"/>Porphyrio <lb n="4"/>pro salutem <note>sic</note> <lb n="5"/>suam <note>sic</note> et suorum <lb n="6"/>ex imperio Hero<lb break="no" n="7"/>nis <expan><abbr>lib</abbr><ex>ens</ex></expan> animo feci <lb n="8"/>Glabrione et Homu<lb break="no" n="9"/>l<expan><ex>l</ex><abbr>o</abbr></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>In mehrere Teile gebrochen. Oberhalb der Inschrift Reliefdarstellung eines Reiters. Hederae als Worttrenner. Z. 6: animo mit AN-Ligatur. (B): Pippidi; AE 1962: a&amp;lt;n&amp;gt;i{i}mo.</p>
            </div>
